Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.87,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,FAMOUS DETECTIVE HOLMES
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.08,0:01:40.98,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Missing Freight Car!?\NThe Professor's Big Magic Trick
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.58,0:01:54.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:01:58.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.86,0:02:08.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody!\NPut that gold back in the boxes quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.30,0:02:18.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:21.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll become an instant millionaire,\Nif I steal all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.68,0:02:25.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be able to eat a trainload of candies\Nand ice cream, as much as I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.38,0:02:32.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to make those two dolts work\Nin order to make my plan successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.35,0:02:34.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.52,0:02:36.58,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes!\N- Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.58,0:02:51.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All passengers taking\Nthe train to London...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.37,0:02:53.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the train is arriving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.38,0:03:03.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The freight car is sandwiched\Nbetween two passenger trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.15,0:03:07.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they must be carrying\Ngold, silver or some treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.51,0:03:31.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We will never know what might happen\Nuntil we arrive in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.61,0:03:34.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please protect the gold bullion,\Neven at the risk of your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.18,0:03:35.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.50,0:04:27.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for me to shock people all\Nover London and all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.13,0:04:28.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I will complete the perfect crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.35,0:04:41.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is anything wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:43.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.68,0:04:45.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I just saw something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.32,0:04:47.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The people I hate\Nare on this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.14,0:05:05.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.24,0:05:08.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.84,0:05:11.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Chicken!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! Get down! Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.82,0:05:22.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Tunnel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.53,0:05:32.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.23,0:05:33.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.13,0:05:34.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.10,0:05:35.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:36.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.01,0:05:44.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:52.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be arriving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.25,0:05:55.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We just passed Newton station,\Ndidn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.59,0:05:57.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We're close to the\NKenyon junction point.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.59,0:05:59.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we'll be in time\Nfor a late night dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:03.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, Mrs. Hudson will be\Nmaking a late night dinner for us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:05.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I sent her a telegraph at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.07,0:06:10.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, that's not a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.41,0:06:16.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\NWe must have a bad train engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.65,0:06:19.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly hit the\Nbrake going downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.25,0:06:30.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A warm meat pie and milk tea!\NThat doesn't sound bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.93,0:06:38.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:58.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not there!\NThe freight car is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:06:59.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:03.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:05.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the train that departed\Nfrom Liverpool at 5:25 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.33,0:07:08.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and arrived at London\Nat 10:37 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:09.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!\NBut...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.50,0:07:10.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.03,0:07:12.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me! I have no idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.97,0:07:16.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You! This train carried one\Nfreight car. Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.50,0:07:19.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to transport gold bullion\Nit's connected as the fourth car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.14,0:07:21.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\NThe freight car is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:23.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We should call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.14,0:07:24.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The freight car is more important\Nthan calling the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:25.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the freight car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.51,0:07:26.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking the wrong person!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:29.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me,\Nis there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.15,0:07:32.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The freight car is missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.35,0:07:34.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It vanished like a ghost,\Nwith a huge amount of gold bullion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.46,0:07:35.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold bullion?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:39.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.\NI'm sure I saw one freight car before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.93,0:07:42.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A missing freight car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.63,0:07:45.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but you might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.70,0:07:47.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.90,0:07:49.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.24,0:07:51.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the famous\Nprivate detective, Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.41,0:07:54.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help me!\NPlease find the freight car!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.31,0:07:57.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that it must be fate that\NI happened to be on this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.48,0:07:58.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:24.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A rope mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.05,0:08:40.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.32,0:08:42.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All passengers!\NPlease wait for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.59,0:08:43.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to ask\Neverybody some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.49,0:08:49.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the famous detective\Nis already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.70,0:08:52.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I just happened\Nto be on this train, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:55.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then can I ask some questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.57,0:08:59.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The freight car was connected between\Nthe front and rear passenger cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.91,0:09:01.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And it disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.34,0:09:04.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There were passenger cars\Nin front and back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.88,0:09:06.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Where has it gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.45,0:09:08.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The train was running on the rail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.75,0:09:10.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If one successfully detached the cars,\Nthere are still passenger cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.95,0:09:12.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,on both front and backside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:14.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nowhere for\Nthe freight car to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.79,0:09:16.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.73,0:09:18.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find out anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.96,0:09:21.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned that when we passed\NNewton station and Kenyon junction...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.80,0:09:23.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the freight car was still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.63,0:09:30.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And they said the freight car\Nwas gone at Burton Moss station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:40.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the freight car disappeared\Nbetween the junction & Burton Moss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:45.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But how?\NWho did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.99,0:09:49.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one person who could\Nthink up this type of bold crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.12,0:09:51.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and actually commit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.66,0:09:54.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Moriarty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.27,0:10:01.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:08.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gently...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.34,0:10:10.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.13,0:10:26.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.96,0:10:28.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the other boxes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.43,0:10:29.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:30.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:38.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:40.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pile of gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.44,0:10:42.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's gold!\NGold! Gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.64,0:10:43.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pile of gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.88,0:10:45.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally became a millionaire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:48.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold! Gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.05,0:10:50.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor! We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.92,0:10:53.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally victorious after having\Nbeen patient in this poor life!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:56.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! And this victory is because of\Nmy artistic talent for crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.79,0:10:59.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Holmes won't\Nfigure out this trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.09,0:11:00.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and he'll run away from the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:11.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And do you think you can figure\Nout where the freight car is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.84,0:11:15.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm planning to check between the\Ntwo stations tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.81,0:11:20.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.01,0:11:22.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's an interesting idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.98,0:11:25.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I recycled my old gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.19,0:11:31.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They're very unique kitchen gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.19,0:11:32.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you playing with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.69,0:11:35.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry. This is really unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:37.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think so?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.73,0:11:39.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you eat it\Nwhile it's still warm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.87,0:11:43.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we will be very busy tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.62,0:11:59.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like I thought. The rail road\Ntracks split off in several directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.52,0:12:02.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. There are so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:07.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Those are for the coal mines\Nand iron factories around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.79,0:12:11.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the freight car was separated\Nand sent on one of the sidetracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.43,0:12:12.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.27,0:12:14.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But how could they separate the\None car from the rest of the train?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.53,0:12:15.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.40,0:12:18.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.\NIt's still working.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.17,0:12:25.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But Holmes, if you change tracks, all\Nthe cars would go onto the sidetrack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.15,0:12:29.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the rope marks\NI found between the passenger cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.29,0:12:33.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,First, they tied with rope between\Nthe two passenger cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.35,0:12:34.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,in front and behind the freight car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.16,0:12:36.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just like Mrs. Hudson's\Nkitchen gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.92,0:12:38.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. It means that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.66,0:12:42.43,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,Liverpool station had tight security,\Nso they did it after the train departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.93,0:12:46.30,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody tied the front and\Nback passenger cars with rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.20,0:12:50.83,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,After the train passed Kenyon Junction\Nand came on the top of the hill...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.90,0:12:53.53,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,they disconnected the front\Nand backside of the freight car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.91,0:12:56.97,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,After Kenyon Junction,\Nit was all downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.54,0:13:00.64,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,While the train passed,\Nthey separated the freight car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:03.82,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,And the person who was waiting there\Nswitched tracks and the freight car...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:05.65,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,went onto the sidetrack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:11.55,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,The rear passenger cars were pulled\Nby the rope and accelerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.63,0:13:14.49,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,When the engineer applied the brake,\Nthe cars automatically joined together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:20.66,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember feeling a jolt\Naround that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.37,0:13:24.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,When you said the driver was\Nnot very skilful using the brake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.44,0:13:26.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We should have checked\Nwhen that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:28.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now all we just have to do\Nis follow the sidetrack...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.38,0:13:29.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,to find the missing freight car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.42,0:13:38.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody must be\Nusing a blast furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:41.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave ho! Heave ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.56,0:13:42.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:44.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to get the gold out\Nbefore people find us here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.56,0:13:51.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.43,0:13:54.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!\NDo it quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.50,0:13:55.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too hungry to move!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.80,0:13:56.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel dizzy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.60,0:13:58.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.57,0:14:02.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Steak! Or at least some sausage!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.08,0:14:06.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!\NI'll go and get something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.52,0:14:10.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But you should continue working.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.42,0:14:14.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't give you any gold\Nunless you finish on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.99,0:14:16.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.43,0:14:22.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I only have this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.37,0:14:30.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If I exchanged the gold into money,\NI'd be a millionaire. How shameful!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:43.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, I don't even have any gas.\NI don't like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.52,0:14:54.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect that we could use\NMrs. Hudson's dinner here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.96,0:14:56.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, I feel it will be a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.73,0:14:57.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.46,0:14:59.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't finish before the\NProfessor comes back...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.50,0:15:01.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,he won't let us eat anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.44,0:15:05.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.54,0:15:06.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:07.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.14,0:15:12.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Moriarty asked\Nus to deliver this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:13.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.21,0:15:14.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:16.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.82,0:15:19.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's gorgeous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.59,0:15:22.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There's also some wine here.\NHe's acting like a millionaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.89,0:15:25.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's very generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.66,0:15:30.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,\Nwhere's the Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.43,0:15:32.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.17,0:15:35.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Professor had something to\Ntake care of in London, suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.14,0:15:38.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the Professor was\Nvery cheap and annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.01,0:15:43.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A man shouldn't be\Njudged by his looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.35,0:15:53.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The sleeping pills work best\Nwhen people are hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.80,0:16:06.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.37,0:16:08.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.54,0:16:14.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Rats! I could only buy a little.\NI know they're going to complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.51,0:16:21.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My gold bullion!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.82,0:16:22.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.82,0:16:26.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.22,0:16:28.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you waiting for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.76,0:16:30.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:31.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:41.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!\NDon't let them get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:45.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.91,0:16:48.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.81,0:16:49.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you to get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.84,0:16:50.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:51.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.48,0:16:53.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.19,0:17:01.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.06,0:17:04.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes! Holmes!\NWhere are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.99,0:17:08.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Hudson told me he\Nwent in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.33,0:17:12.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.73,0:17:15.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Lestrade of Scotland Yard\Nwill take the gold bullion!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.44,0:17:24.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.18,0:17:25.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrest them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.43,0:17:43.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:50.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.38,0:17:56.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You villains!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.55,0:18:04.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.60,0:18:21.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Todd! Smiley!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.54,0:18:25.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to rescue the Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:28.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.34,0:18:30.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We never know what he'll do\Nto us when he's very angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.24,0:18:31.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.66,0:18:50.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.10,0:18:52.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.07,0:18:53.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:09.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to do that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.58,0:19:10.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.45,0:19:12.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.19,0:19:16.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.44,0:19:31.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That line just goes around the old\Nstation and comes back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.64,0:19:33.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's relax and wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.10,0:20:01.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.11,0:20:10.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!\NDon't let them escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.31,0:20:15.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.96,0:20:24.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they?\NWhere is Moriarty?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.13,0:20:26.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:38.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:42.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Not again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:43.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.81,0:20:47.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand it any more!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.42,0:20:50.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool! You're in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.28,0:20:51.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.89,0:20:59.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.83,0:21:00.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.43,0:21:01.59,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off! Get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.90,0:21:03.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.\NThen!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.40,0:21:10.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.77,0:21:16.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!\NGo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.11,0:21:17.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave ho! Heave ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.18,0:21:20.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:21.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.06,0:21:33.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not the gold bullion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.43,0:21:34.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.56,0:21:35.59,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.66,0:21:38.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They replaced it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.67,0:21:48.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.78,0:21:50.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious popcorn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.58,0:21:54.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Danger! Danger!\NEverybody take cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.49,0:22:09.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Switching the freight cars\Nwas a successful plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.40,0:22:10.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.23,0:22:13.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But nobody will be able to\Nfinish eating this much popcorn.
